{
  "page": "Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/50px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/75px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/100px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Elder Brother</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/50px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/75px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/100px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Pojypojy_B%26Elder_Brother.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Pojypojy B&amp;Elder Brother.JPG\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4e/Pojypojy_B%26Elder_Brother.JPG/350px-Pojypojy_B%26Elder_Brother.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"/images/4/4e/Pojypojy_B%26Elder_Brother.JPG 1.5x\" /></a><div>The Elder Brother and <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, by Pojypojy ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother\" title=\"Elder Brother\">Elder Brother</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> (formerly)</li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_256_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">256&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <small>(age 44)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ian_McShane\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ian McShane\">Ian McShane</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_6\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 6\">Season 6</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Elder Brother</b> is the leader of a <a href=\"/index.php/Septry\" title=\"Septry\">septry</a> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a>. He is reputed to have powers as a healer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> This <a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother\" title=\"Elder Brother\">elder brother's</a> given name is unknown.\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>, the Elder Brother is merged with <a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">Meribald</a> as <b>Ray</b>, and portrayed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ian_McShane\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ian McShane\">Ian McShane</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Elder Brother is a tall man, with a large, square head, shrewd eyes, a veiny red nose, and a heavy jaw. He shaves his head into a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/tonsure\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:tonsure\">tonsure</a>, but his scalp is stubbly, as is his jawline. He looks more like a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> than a holy man, and moves with the strength of a man in his prime.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He used to be a drunkard, and is ashamed of his past behavior. He believes he began a second life after he \"died\" in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Trident\" title=\"Battle of the Trident\">Battle of the Trident</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Elder Brother was born the third son of a family of knights, and his father, grandfather, and brothers were all knights. He was trained to fight from the day he was old enough to hold a wooden <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">sword</a>. He saw many battles, and did well in them, without disgrace. However, he had some women by rape, which he now considers shameful. When he was not fighting, he was drunk. He wished to marry a younger daughter of a petty <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>, but as a third son, he had nothing to offer her but the <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a>, sword, and <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a> of his knighthood.\n</p><p>He fought for <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Trident\" title=\"Battle of the Trident\">Battle of the Trident</a>, serving a lord who served a lord who chose to support King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a> rather than <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert Baratheon</a>. He was shot in the thigh and the foot, and his horse was killed, but he still fought, while desperate to find another horse, as he could not afford a new one and could not be a knight without a horse. A blow from behind knocked him unconscious, and he fell into the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>. Others thought him dead, so they stripped his <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a> and possessions and pushed his body into deeper waters. He floated downstream where he woke up naked on the <a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a>. He spent the next ten years as a penitent under a vow of silence.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At some point he became the <a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother\" title=\"Elder Brother\">Elder Brother</a> of the Quiet Isle, and took residence in the cave called the Hermit's Hole. He gained a reputation as a great healer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Hyle_Hunt\" title=\"Hyle Hunt\">Hyle Hunt</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">Meribald</a> come to the <a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a> and meet with the Elder Brother. When Brienne tells the Elder Brother that she is seeking <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a>, he tells them of the <a href=\"/index.php/Raid_on_Saltpans\" title=\"Raid on Saltpans\">raid on Saltpans</a>, and invites them to pray for the people of <a href=\"/index.php/Saltpans\" title=\"Saltpans\">Saltpans</a> and to stay for dinner at the <a href=\"/index.php/Septry\" title=\"Septry\">septry</a>. After supper, the Elder Brother has his <a href=\"/index.php/Proctor\" title=\"Proctor\">proctor</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Narbert\" title=\"Narbert\">Narbert</a>, guide Brienne's male companions to their pallets in the cloisters, but the Elder Brother walks with Brienne to the cottages on the Isle where she will sleep.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the cottage, the Elder Brother asks Brienne asks why she is looking for Sandor Clegane at Saltpans. She explains that she is looking for \"a <a href=\"/index.php/Highborn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Highborn\">highborn</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Maid\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maid\">maid</a> of three-and-ten, with a fair face and auburn hair,\" a description that the Elder Brother immediately recognizes as <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a>. He informs Brienne that what she had heard from <a href=\"/index.php/Timeon\" title=\"Timeon\">Timeon</a> was incorrect, that it was actually <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> whom Sandor had held captive. The Elder Brother also tells Brienne that the man she seeks is dead. He says that he had found Sandor dying by the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>, and attempted to heal his wounds, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Hound\" title=\"Hound\">Hound</a> died in his arms. The Elder Brother says that he buried Sandor and left his Hound <a href=\"/index.php/Helm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Helm\">helm</a> to mark his grave, which he feels was a great error as <a href=\"/index.php/Rorge\" title=\"Rorge\">another</a> took it to wear to raid Saltpans, and that Sandor is innocent of that crime.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Elder Brother then tells Brienne of his own life, and how it changed after he \"died\" in the Battle of the Trident. He asks Brienne to give up her quest to find Sansa and return home, saying that <a href=\"/index.php/Selwyn_Tarth\" title=\"Selwyn Tarth\">her father</a> would rather have a living daughter than her broken <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a>. To this, Brienne tearfully confesses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\">her family's</a> sad history and her life since she left <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>, and that she must find Sansa or die trying.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Brienne and her companions leave the Quiet Isle, Brienne thinks that the Elder Brother had at least convinced her not to look for Sansa along the Trident. She wonders if she should return <a href=\"/index.php/Oathkeeper\" title=\"Oathkeeper\">Oathkeeper</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> and return home as the Elder Brother had urged.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/The_Seven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Seven\">The Seven</a> have blessed our Elder Brother with healing hands. He has restored many a man to health that even the <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maesters</a> could not cure, and many a woman too.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Narbert\" title=\"Narbert\">Narbert</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He looks more like a man made to break bones than to heal one, thought the Maid of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>, as the Elder Brother strode across the room to embrace <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meribald\" title=\"Meribald\">Meribald</a> and pat <a href=\"/index.php/Dog_(Meribald)\" title=\"Dog (Meribald)\">Dog</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Rorge\" title=\"Rorge\">The man</a> who <a href=\"/index.php/Raid_on_Saltpans\" title=\"Raid on Saltpans\">raped and killed</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Saltpans\" title=\"Saltpans\">Saltpans</a> was not <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a>, though he may be as dangerous. The <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> are full of such scavengers. I will not call them <a href=\"/index.php/Wolves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wolves\">wolves</a>. Wolves are nobler than that... and so are <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a>, I think.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the Elder Brother, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Brienne:</b> You sound as if you pity <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">him</a>.<br />\n<b>Elder Brother:</b> I did. You would have pitied him as well, if you had seen him at the end. I came upon him by the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>, drawn by his cries of pain. He begged me for the <a href=\"/index.php/Gift_of_mercy\" title=\"Gift of mercy\">gift of mercy</a>, but I am sworn not to kill again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> and the Elder Brother</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Brienne:</b> It is true, then. Sandor Clegane is dead.<br />\n<b>Elder Brother:</b> He is at rest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> and the Elder Brother</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>All in all, I was a sad man. When I was not fighting, I was drunk. My life was writ in red, in blood and <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the Elder Brother, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Trident\" title=\"Battle of the Trident\">The battle</a> was a bloody thing. The singers would have us believe it was all <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert</a> struggling in <a href=\"/index.php/Ruby_ford\" title=\"Ruby ford\">the stream</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Lyanna_Stark\" title=\"Lyanna Stark\">a woman</a> both of them claimed to love, but I assure you, other men were fighting too, and I was one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the Elder Brother, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We are all born naked, so I suppose it was only fitting that I come into my second life the same way.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the Elder Brother, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Go <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">home</a>, child. You have a home, which is more than many can say in these dark days.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the Elder Brother, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: External links\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Ray\">Ray</a> on the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Wiki_of_Westeros\">Wiki of Westeros</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued)#Elder_Brother_.28Quiet_Isle.29\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued)\">Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.02</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.03</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.04</a></su